1998-12-07 01:04  jgarzik

	* COPYING: GNOME-standard autogen.sh scripts automatically run
	'automake -a'.	-a installs any necessary files that are required
	in a GNU-standard install, such as COPYING, INSTALL, mkinstalldirs,
	etc.
	
	So begone, automake-installed files.

